{
  "text": "MAPbI 3 -0P, MAPbI 3 -0.5P, MAPbI 3 -1P, and MAPbI 3 -10P OIHP thin films were prepared by the (anti)solvent-assisted one-step spin-coating method. [CITATION_1] A base MAPbI 3 -0.5P, MAPbI 3 -1P, and MAPbI 3 -10P solutions, 0.003, 0.006, and 0.031 g of Pluronic P123 was added, respectively. Subsequently, the precursor solutions were spin-coated at 4,000 rpm for 30 s on appropriate substrates. At 7 s after the start of the spin-coating step, 0.6 mL of chlorobenzene was quickly dripped. The spin-coated thin films were then annealed at 130 C for 5 min.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "205410102"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "205410102": {
      "title": "Solvent engineering for high-performance inorganicorganic hybrid perovskite solar cells",
      "abstract": "The performance of solar cells based on organic–inorganic perovskites strongly depends on the device architecture and processing conditions. It is now shown that solvent engineering enables the deposition of very dense perovskite layers on mesoporous titania, leading to photovoltaic devices with a high light-conversion efficiency and no hysteresis."
    }
  }
}